<DATELINE>GAZA CITY, Occupied Gaza Strip (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Two Palestinians fighting deportation orders pleaded their case Sunday in an open hearing _ the first time the army permitted the public to attend an appeals session. Defense lawyers lauded the army's decision but said due process was still being violated because prosecutors could submit `` secret evidence'' without having to show it to the defense. <PERSON> Said </PERSON> <PERSON> Barakat </PERSON>, 32, a Moslem fundamentalist leader, and <PERSON> Riad </PERSON> <PERSON> Adjour </PERSON>, 26, accused of being a <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> activist, are among 25 Palestinians from the Israeli-occupied <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> fighting deportation orders issued last month. Since the Dec. 8 start of the Palestinian uprising in the occupied territories, <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> has expelled 33 Arabs. The practice has been denounced by the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and other Western nations as violating international human rights conventions. `` There is no hope, no justice for me here, but I do n't want to go without fighting,'' <PERSON> Barakat </PERSON> told the tribunal. The hearing before a three-member military review committee took place at the army's <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> headquarters and was attended by three journalists and about two dozen relatives of the defendants. <PERSON> Barakat </PERSON> and <PERSON> Adjour </PERSON> sat quietly on a wooden bench as the prosecutor, Capt. <PERSON> Meir </PERSON> <PERSON> Klinger </PERSON>, read the charges against them. <PERSON> Klinger </PERSON> said <PERSON> Barakat </PERSON>, a high school teacher from the <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> town of <PERSON> Bani </PERSON> <PERSON> Suheila </PERSON>, was a chief ideologust of <ORGANIZATION> Islamic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jihad </ORGANIZATION>, a Moslem fundamentalist org