 power should have been cut off by automatic current limiters that act when a cable gets hot. Electricity also continued to flow through a nearby <ORGANIZATION> Metro </ORGANIZATION> transit cable, powering electric trolleys, and that may have made the fire worse, he said. When the power restoration began, patrols roamed the area to make sure no fires were triggered by equipment left switched on when the outage began. `` It went very smoothly. I have no reports of problems other than the sprinkler in the Battery Street tunnel,'' which apparently began wetting down the tunnel when it was tripped by the power surge, <PERSON> McIntosh </PERSON> said. `` We called the fire department and told them it was their problem.'' Air conditioning was lost as temperatures soared to a September record of 98 degrees Friday and to a record for the date of 92 on Saturday. Sunday dawned with a cool fog and a forecast high of only 80 to 85. City Light had no estimate of its costs to restore power or of damage from the fire. `` Our field people were really extending themselves, a lot of them volunteering to go 16 hours, double shifts, until they could get the thing done,'' <PERSON> McIntosh </PERSON> said. No injuries were reported and stepped-up police patrols were credited with preventing break-ins. At the height of the blackout, city officials estimated that 90 percent of all businesses in the area were closed. The area has about 130 restaurants, 55 shops in the popular Pike Place Market, the large <PERSON> Bon </PERSON> <PERSON> Marche </PERSON> department store and several hotels, grocery stores and taverns. Pike Place Market businesses saw a drop in traffic, even though many shops never lost electricity. `` People think the whole market is closed,'' said <PERSON> Garth </PERSON> <PERSON> Wilson </PERSON> of <PERSON> Jack </PERSON>'s Fish Spot. The <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cross </ORGANIZATION> served three meals a day to 150 to 250 elderly residents stuck in the darkened area. Volunteers had to take some meals up 13 flights in buildings where elevators were out of operation.
